cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM 

This paper deals with the problem of single-view 3D shape completion and reconstruction using deep generative models and adversarially learned shape priors. This involves computer vision (CV) techniques for processing 2D images and generating 3D shapes, as well as machine learning (ML) techniques for training deep generative models and learning shape priors. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves graphics (GR) techniques for visualizing 3D shapes, and learning (LG) techniques for training deep generative models and shape priors. The paper also involves AI techniques for generating plausible 3D shapes, and multimedia (MM) techniques for processing and visualizing 2D and 3D data. Therefore, cs.GR, cs.LG, cs.AI, and cs.MM are also likely sub-categories.
